<br>
Cazic turned out to be a major set back in my opinion, because we had to re-kill all the creatures that popped again.  Also because he likes to zap people (instant death) either because he is protecting his little fellows or he is sick and twisted and enjoys killing people (You decide :P) )  And being short Tanks and Clerics, we couldn't take out Dracoliche who seems to enjoy telling Cazic we are here after he picks up the rumors from the various creatures that wander in the planes.  This also cut down the area of creatures I could pull, or least pull them in a timely manner.<br>
<br>
We had a few setup backs which is normal for the planes.  Our biggest problem (I'm not critizing anyone, just bringing this up because this is a learning experience) was pets on the wrong target.  Just something for you to keep in mind if your a pet caster, it is critical for you to keep your pet under control so our enchanter does get unneccessarily beat up and chews up all our clerics mana.<br>
<br>
I was also surpised at the number of no shows, roughly 18 people I expected to show up, didn't.  Oh well, live and learn.  I think I will invite up to 45 people next time, which should compensate for no shows.<br>
<br>
I would like to thank all who attending, and Harbingers for co-sponsoring this event.  I am going to organize my paperwork talk to a few people, then try to set up another one for PoF in two weeks.<br>
<br>
And my apologize to everyone for the skimpy treasure.  We technically had to kill the same creatures twice, yet it seems like we barely received treasure normally obtained in killing them once.  Oh well, just a little unlucky this time I guess.<br>
<br>
Zellex <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ujzonn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jzonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/17/00 1:30:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personal.bhm.bellsouth.net/bhm/r/p/rpo2/Jzonn_Icon.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 5/17/00 PoF Recap</span><hr size=1> As one of the participants, I had a blast.  Personally, I died five times, but still managed to make about a half bubble of exp.  I didn't win any of the Ranger lottos, but I'm happy for those who did.  I have several screen shots.  Once I review them, converted to jpegs, and ordered; I'll get them somewhere for everyone to see.  I'm pleased to get some nice shots of Cazic and Draco (using Bind Sight).<br>
<br>
I was asked to lead one of the Fear groups and I consider it an honor to do so.  Lirpa had no knowledge of my abilities or temperment.  I did this function the whole time except for a brief stint when I had a major thunderstorm came across and knocked out power four times in a row (before I could get back into EQ).  Cronis led the group during this time and for a short time after (until he went LD).<br>
<br>
I signed on just after 1PM CST and hussled over to the Fear portal (I camped in Oggok at the end of my last EQ session).  We organized and prepped for the entry and my group (the second group to enter) went in at 3:11:10PM CST.  We made it to the north camp, but one of my group members (not sure who and it doesn't matter) aggroed several nasties over to the camp.  Kartain and I were alread at the camp and beginning the camp out, but we all died.  By 4:15PM CST everyone was ressed and we were prepping again.  We started the clear at around 4:45PM CST.  I spent my time practicing my hand-to-hand on the bouncers in Oggok.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
While still at the north camp, the party was wiped out by some roamers on the east side of Fear.  As I understand it, we stayed too long at the north camp after clearing out some of the west side.  This happened twice before we finally moved to the NW corner.  After moving to the NW corner, we cleared out some of the west side and then Cazic decided to make an appearance.  We made a mad dash back to the north camp and began the process of clearing the zone once again.  This time with the watchful eye of Cazic and his special welcome to anyone he discovers in his zone.<br>
<br>
We cleared the zone again with the occasional death touch (DT) from Cazic.  Only one time to he start chain DTing and we camped out after the first two.  We cleared and made it back to the NW corner.  At this point, Draco decided to roam around a bit.  Eventually, he made it to the area we were set up.  Unfortunately, he brought some friends along with him.  Any member Draco didn't get, his friends finished off.  One Cleric made it out safely and the ressing process began anew.<br>
<br>
The Monks resumed the pulling and it was pretty much standard pulling tactics.  They would pull things, Lirpa would mes the extras, and we would kill them as we could.  Every so often, there would be a breakdown and the group would be fighting multiples.  At one point, the main tank (Ranstorm) had to leave to eat.  I was asked to be the main tank.  *puffs up*  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It was quite exciting and a major challenge (more on this in the 'observations' section of this post).  Eventually, we cleared enough where we could move to the west camp.<br>
<br>
With the exception of one more pull where just about everyone died, the pulls were handled fine.  Somewhere in all of this, I stopped keeping track (time wise) of when things happened.  I knew what time it was, but I just stopped noting it.  More clears and we moved to a south camp next to the scareling tower.<br>
<br>
At the south tower we had our last major incident (before I left Fear).  Several Amy warriors were pulled and an immediate camp out was called.  I managed to make it out.  After we all were back in and everyone was ressed, we continued the pulls.  I started getting punchy at this point.  I still managed to go another hour and a half, but by 4AM CST, I was all spent (I had been up since 6AM the morning before).  After getting a port to Lava, I camped and went to bed.  And thus ended my first foray into the Plane of Fear.<br>
<br>
&quot;But what did you observe?&quot;, you may ask.  I'll tell ya.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
First, I think Lirpa, Zellek, and Kexian did an outstanding job in organizing and running the raid.  While I've done a lot of research on Fear, it is very nice to have someone there who knows what is going on.  I learned a lot on how an event like this could (and, I think, should) go.  Could I run one of these?  To an extent, yes.  I need a couple more under my belt to cover some things I've not experienced yet.<br>
<br>
Second, people need to learn to follow orders.  And I do not mean directions, I mean orders.  If people cannot follow an order, they don't need to be there.  There are a couple people who I would have rooted if I could have...*particularly* after Cazic spawned.  We also had a few loots done by someone who was the same class as the armor drops from that particular mob.  Nothing happened, it was just a standard order:  Don't loot a mob if it drops your classes armor.  And then a situation with people attacking a mob (in a multi-pull) before the main tank acquired a target.<br>
<br>
Third, it was very difficult to aquire a target to attack at times.  There would be times, after I had hit the assist hotkey three times, where I still didn't have a target to attack.  I could look and see the main tank hitting the mob in front of me and I would use my 'target nearest NPC' button and it wouldn't work.  *That* was frustrating.  There was also a lot of running around to follow a mob as it jumped from one area to another, particularly the scarelings.<br>
<br>
Fourth, the loot drops were terrible in comparison to what I had heard about for a normal Fear raid.  Certainly, I've heard of variations this low.  It's just disappointing to actually be on a raid where it happens.  This is not the fault of the event managers, though.  Just the way it works sometimes.<br>
<br>
Overall, I had a great time.  I ready to do it again.  Do I expect it to be the same every time?  Not on your life.  It will be a different challenge each time and I want to learn about them.  I met a bunch of people.  I lost a good bit of sleep.  I went through a lot of caffeine.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If you need my services again, just let me know. <p><B><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#004080">Jzonn Stormwolf &lt;Avenging Crusaders&gt;</B></FONT><BR>
<I><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE=2 COLOR="#a0a0a0">Ranger of Karana</I></FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhaemish.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haemish</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/17/00 3:20:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.godwin.com/sd/haemish.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 5/17/00 PoF Recap</span><hr size=1> Jzonn, send me the screenshots at haemish@mail.com and I'll put them on the Council web site under the gallery. That space is there, we might as well use it, and since there were a good number of Council members there, we should post some on the web site. <br>
