Kordail O`Brien <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CBC6B1><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Kartain</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br> <font color=#8E9173>(7/20/00 12:09:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsevents.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> My views. (longer than expected)</span><hr size=1> Since this raid I've been on 3 or 4 more, maybe 5 I can't remember. We all know you can't get enough clerics in Fear due to nothing there for us to loot except the belt (and I still haven't gotten one). Anyway due to the downtime of the servers I figured now would be a good time to point out my observations.<br>
<br>
I've seen different ways of doing things on each raid and a few of them just seem to work better than others.<br>
<br>
1. Mass raid on break-in compared to group by group.<br>
a. Group by group seemed to work the best. Give the mob time to settle down and send in the next group just works the best hands down. <br>
b. By doing a mass gang-buster style break-in you end bringing all the mobs with you and kill whomever is already there camping. It only takes a few hits and the mobs move on to the next living person. Be it somebody half way through camp or somebody that's just making it there, 30 seconds is just to long to try to make it out using this style.<br>
<br>
2. This one is basically an observation of mine but if the situation should arise again maybe it'll be remembered.<br>
<br>
Last night we had a premo mix of people but myself I didn't think the grouping was exactly top-notch, not to say it was wrong but that I think it could have been better. We had a bard and 2 chanters, awesome I think. The primary chanter handled the buffs in her group and what others she could while the secondary handled the buffs for most everybody else. Both were run through the hoops on keeping everybody buffed. All this while the bard was busy playing manasong for our group which stayed almost FM the majority of the time, but one problem, no chanter in our group. I feel that if you have a bard and enchanter they should be in the same group so that the enchanter can keep up with the mana required to keep everybody buffed.<br>
<br>
3. Pet control.<br>
I've seen it on every raid, pet control is a REQUIREMENT!!! People please understand this. I know it's been stated over and over but there is a constant problem with pets. I don't have a solution to the problem but I've got a few ideas that may help some. The /assist command is essential to a successful mission. So far I've only used it one way, assist on the main tank. There may be another way to do this but not sure how well it would work. If all tanks hot keyed the main tank and each group member assist that groups main tank. As an example I'm in a group with Jzonn as the leader and the main tank is Damin (that's a scary thought already). I hot key Jzonn on my assist while he hot keys Damin. It may take a second more for everyone to get on target but that second may make the difference in getting on the right mob and not getting it. It may also have a side benefit. If the main tank goes LD we don't have a clue till somebody shouts it. Till then we sit and wait since we don't have a target, at least those of us that don't start nuking at the first sight of a mob. As the tanks get more used to how each other fight then you'll know if the main tank hasn't targeted the mob as quickly as he/she normally does. The secondary tank takes over here. Every group member doesn't have to keep up with who is who except for the tanks. If all the tanks are doing their job and are assisting the correct person then mob death should come as quickly as it had before the main tank went LD without a pet getting on the wrong mob. In theory I think it would work but don't know for fact that it will. The only real drawback to this is if the main tank of the group goes LD then the group is lost. Give me some feedback on this one and tell me what you think.<br>
<br>
