<br>
9. Members.<br>
Give your leader an idea of how long you plan on staying. Be it 30 minutes or until it's over. Give people a chance to plan group movement before you leave. I know it's not always possible to predict when you have to leave due to real life situations but if at all possible don't wait till the last second to tell someone you are leaving. This also gives us an idea if you are coming back if you go LD. Give feedback to your group on anything you require which includes giving your mana report. If you are diseased, let somebody know. If you are buffless and shouldn't be, let somebody know. If you are at 20% mana, let somebody know. Communication is the key to a successful mission, please use it more. I could go on about this one for hours but I think you get my drift.<br>
